+# Linguist sample-file selection
+
+Linguist trains its language classifier on real-world samples stored under
+`samples/<Language>/` in the Linguist repo. For a new language a handful of
+representative files is enough.
+
+## What Linguist expects
+
+- At least one sample under `samples/Sen STL/`.
+- Prefer 3-5 files covering the declaration kinds (struct, enum, variant,
+  class, interface, quantity, alias). Short files are fine.
+- **Do not** include samples that would also parse as stereolithography STL.
+  Every sample must start with a `package` declaration or contain a clear
+  STL declaration keyword near the top, so the heuristic picks Sen STL.
+
+## Candidate files in the Sen repository
+
+These are good candidates because they are small, cover different declaration
+kinds, and use the canonical Sen style. Copy them verbatim into Linguist's
+`samples/Sen STL/` directory as part of the PR.
+
+| Sen repo path                                    | Why include it                                |
+| ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
+| `stl/sen/kernel/build_info.stl`                  | Canonical struct with enums and imports.      |
+| `stl/sen/kernel/kernel_api.stl`                  | Class with methods, events, attributes.       |
+| `stl/sen/kernel/basic_types.stl`                 | Quantities, aliases, primitive types.         |
+| `stl/sen/transport/*.stl` (pick one)             | Larger real-world file with inheritance.      |
+| `components/term/stl/term.stl` (if applicable)   | Variant + tagged-union style.                 |
+
+Adjust the list before submission if any of these paths have changed; the
+point is to show Linguist the full syntactic surface so its classifier does
+not confuse `.stl` with stereolithography even for files that do not start
+with `package`.
+
+## Checklist
+
+1. Copy selected files into `samples/Sen STL/` in your Linguist fork,
+   keeping original filenames.
+2. Run `bundle exec rake samples` to update the classifier index.
+3. Run `bundle exec rake test` and ensure the new samples classify as
+   `Sen STL`.
